---
kind: skill
version: "1.0"
name: golden-skill
description: "Reference skill exercising every SkillConfig field."

# Group 1: Identity (continued)
when-to-use: "Invoke this skill when you need a reference for every skill field."
license: MIT

# Group 3: Tool Access
allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep]

# Group 4: Permissions & Invocation Control
disable-model-invocation: false
user-invocable: true
argument-hint: "Provide a task description as the argument."

# Group 7: Composition / Supporting Files
references: [docs/reference.md, docs/glossary.md]
scripts: [scripts/helper.sh]
assets: [assets/template.txt]
examples: [examples/output.md]

# Group 9: Multi-Target overrides
targets:
  claude:
    suppress-fidelity-warnings: false
    skip-synthesis: false
    instructions-override: ""
    provider:
      custom-key: "claude-skill-value"
  antigravity:
    suppress-fidelity-warnings: true
---
# Golden Skill

This body becomes the skill's instructions at compile time.

1. Step one: read the input.
2. Step two: transform it.
3. Step three: return the result.
